"title": "6135: coveting, and other sins",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6135: coveting, and other sins",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Covetousness is associated with other sins and brings trouble with it.</p>\n<h2>Coveting is linked with other sins</h2>\n<h3>Idolatry</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:5\">EPH 5:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:6-1Cor10:7\">1CO 10:6–10:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:5\">COL 3:5</a></p>\n<h3>Pride</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps10:3\">PSA 10:3</a></p>\n<h3>Sexual sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:28\">MAT 5:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:5\">1TH 4:5</a></p>\n<h3>Laziness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:25-Prov21:26\">PRO 21:25–21:26</a></p>\n<h2>Covetousness is one of many sins which pollute a person</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:21-Mark7:23\">MRK 7:21–7:23</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Love of money is covetousness</h2>\n<h3>It is a source of evil</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:9-1Tim6:10\">1TI 6:9–6:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:2\">PRO 10:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:16\">PRO 22:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:20\">PRO 28:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:22\">PRO 28:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:8-Prov30:9\">PRO 30:8–30:9</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of those who love money</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:14\">LUK 16:14</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:5-John12:6\">JHN 12:5–12:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:25\">MAT 23:25</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:39\">LUK 11:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:3\">2PE 2:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:14\">2PE 2:14</a> <em>False teachers are “experts in greed”.</em></p>\n<h3>Believers must not be lovers of money</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:5\">HEB 13:5</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:2\">1PE 5:2</a></strong> <em>Elders must not be greedy for money.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod18:21\">EXO 18:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:3\">EPH 5:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:1-1Tim3:3\">1TI 3:1–3:3</a></p>\n<h3>Love of money characterises the last days</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:1-2Tim3:2\">2TI 3:1–3:2</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Coveting brings trouble</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:1-Jas4:2\">JAS 4:1–4:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:27\">PRO 15:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:25\">PRO 28:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:4\">PRO 29:4</a></p>\n<h2>Even a gift can be given covetously</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor9:5\">2CO 9:5</a> <em>The gift translated as “one grudgingly given” literally means a “covetous gift”.</em></p>",
